%global packname  wavefunction
%global packver   1.0.0
%global rlibdir   /usr/local/lib/R/library

Name:             R-CRAN-%{packname}
Version:          1.0.0
Release:          1%{?dist}
Summary:          Wave Function Representation of Real Distributions

License:          Apache License (== 2.0)
URL:              https://cran.r-project.org/package=%{packname}
Source0:          %{url}&version=%{packver}#/%{packname}_%{packver}.tar.gz


BuildRequires:    R-devel
Requires:         R-core
BuildArch:        noarch

%description
Real probability distributions can be represented as the square of an
orthogonal sum in the Hermite basis. This representation is formally
similar to the representation of quantum mechanical states as wave
functions, whose squared modulus is a probability density. This is
described in more detail in "Wave function representation of probability
distributions," by Madeleine B. Thompson <arXiv:1712.07764>. This package
provides a reference implementation of the technique.

